  {
    "id": "281fbe0a-b290-8085-be1f-e68d8f371602",
    "title": "Onepeace : The Bridge Between County Hospitals and Hypertension Patients",
    "category": "Projects",
    "organization": "No Org",
    "industry": "Leadership/Community & Business",
    "startDate": "2025-09-12",
    "endDate": "2025-09-23",
    "description": "Onepeace is a value-based digital bridge that connects Community Health Workers (CHWs), hospital EMR systems, and predictive AI in real time.\n\nIt bridges the 20.33% rural healthcare access gap, reduces hypertension complication rates from 76.19% to 31.71% (a 44.48 percentage point improvement), and generates annual healthcare cost savings of $71.65 million.\n\nThis model reduces 10 unnecessary visits per patient annually through early diagnosis and continuous management, saving approximately $4,765 (77% of local annual income).\n\nIt also integrates hidden patients into the healthcare system, simultaneously achieving public health outcomes and fiscal sustainability."
  },
  {
